{{Infobox serial killer |name=Gabriel Garza Hoth |image= |caption= |birthname=Gabriel Garza Hoth |alias=The Black Widower |birth_date= |birth_place=[[Mexico]] |death_date= |death_place= |cause= |conviction= |sentence= |victims=3 |beginyear=1991 |endyear=1998 |country=[[Mexico]] |states= |apprehended= }} '''Gabriel Arturo Garza Hoth''' (born [[Mexico]], ?) also known as "The Black Widower", was a [[Mexicans|Mexican]] [[serial killer]] active between 1991 and 1998 in [[Mexico City]]. He collected life insurance payments on his wife and lovers,<ref>{{cite book |last=Newton |first=Michael |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA346&dq=gabriel+garza+hoth&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=BBF0UoboJKKsjALeloGIAw&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAA |location=New York, USA |publisher=Facts On File, Inc. |isbn=0-8160-6195-5 |accessdate=November 2, 2013 }}</ref> gaining a total of 500,000 dollars.<ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=September 1, 2000 |title=Las ganancias del Viudo Negro |url=http://edant.clarin.com/diario/2000/01/09/e-05802d.htm |newspaper=El Clarín |location=Mexico |publisher= |accessdate=November 2, 2013 }}</ref>
His first victim was his first wife, named Soledad Valdez, who had a heart attack and died in 1991, but the doctors believed that maybe she had been poisoned. His second victim was his girlfriend named Marcela Palacios, who died in 1992 in a "violent assault". The final victim was Ana Gloria Gomezpalacio who died in another "assault".<ref>{{cite news |last=Martínez |first=Fabiola |last2=Baltazar |first2=Elia |last3=Galán |first3=José |date=September 1, 2000 |title=El Viudo Negro, consignado en el Reclusorio Oriente |url=http://www.jornada.unam.mx/2000/01/08/cap4.html |newspaper=La Jornada |location=Mexico |publisher= |accessdate=November 2, 2013 }}</ref> The coincidences were alerted to the police, but Garza escaped to [[Spain]]. He was captured in 1998 and extradited to Mexico, where he was condemned to life in prison.
